author: Aristotle
message: We are what we repeatedly do. Excellence, then, is not an act, but a habit.
title: Thought of the day

author: Ray Bradbury
message: Living at risk is jumping off the cliff and building your wings on the way down.

author: Albert Camus
message: In the depth of winter, I finally learned that there was within me an invincible summer.
title: Thought of the day

author: Madame de Stael
message: Wit lies in recognizing the resemblance among things which differ and the difference between things which are alike.
title: Thought of the day
